'''David Prowse''' ([[July 1]], [[1930s#1935|1935]] - [[November 29|November 28]], [[2020]]) was a bodybuilder and weightlifter who became an actor. He played [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] in the [[original trilogy]].

==Biography==
David Prowse was selected to play [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] due to his height and girth. He would speak the lines from within the suit during filming in his [[Wikipedia:Bristol|Bristol]] accent. However, as this ultimately clashed with [[George Lucas]]'s idea about Vader, [[James Earl Jones]] was dubbed over as Vader's voice &mdash; a fact unknown to Prowse at the time of filming.<ref name="The Guardian obituary">{{WebCite|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/nov/29/david-prowse-obituary|text=David Prowse obituary|author=Gilbey Ryan|work=[[Wikipedia:The Guardian|''The Guardian'']]|date=2010-11-29|archivedate=20201129161544}}</ref><ref name="BBC obituary">{{WebCite|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-55117704|text=Dave Prowse: Darth Vader actor dies aged 85|date=2010-11-29|work=[[Wikipedia:BBC|BBC]]|archivedate=20201130003205}}</ref>

Prowse complains that he never got any publicity as Darth Vader. He had chosen to play Vader because he felt the villain was usually the most memorable.<ref name="BBC obituary" /> Prowse used to attend fan conventions and sign his autographs "David Prowse IS Darth Vader." However, Prowse was banned from official ''Star Wars'' conventions, such as [[Star Wars Weekends|''Star Wars'' Weekends]] in Orlando, by George Lucas, supposedly because of Prowse "annoying" him.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://news.avclub.com/david-prowse-banned-from-all-lucasfilm-related-star-war-1798220912|text=David Prowse banned from all Lucasfilm-related Star Wars events|author=Michelle Welch|date=2010-07-19|work=[[Wikipedia:The A.V. Club|''The A.V. Club'']]|archivedate=20190528133201}}</ref><ref name="The Guardian obituary" />

Prowse died of COVID-19<ref name="Deadline">{{WebCite|url=https://deadline.com/2020/11/david-prowse-darth-vader-covid-coronavirus-cause-of-death-star-wars-1234623134|text='Star Wars' Actor David Prowse Died From Covid-19, Daughter Says – Report|author=Greg Evans|date=2020-11-30|work=[[Wikipedia:Deadline Hollywood|''Deadline'']]|archivedate=20201130163659}}</ref> on November 28, 2020, at 85 years of age.<ref name="Death" /><ref name="The Guardian obituary" /> Several celebrities including Lucas, [[Mark Hamill]], [[Anthony Daniels]], [[W:c:memory-alpha:William Shatner|William Shatner]], [[Rosario Dawson]], and [[Elijah Wood]] paid tribute to Prowse.<ref name="BBC obituary" /><ref>{{WebCite|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/george-lucas-mark-hamill-david-prowse-1234841823|text=George Lucas, Mark Hamill and More Pay Tribute to David Prowse: 'He Made Vader Leap Off the Page'|author=Ellise Shafer|date=2020-11-29|work=[[Wikipedia:Variety (magazine)|''Variety'']]|archivedate=20201130092524}}</ref><ref>{{WebCite|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/11/29/entertainment/david-prowse-darth-vadar-star-wars-dies-gbr-scli-intl/index.html|text=David Prowse, the original Darth Vader, dies aged 85|author=Angela Dewan & Samantha Beech|date=2010-11-29|work=[[Wikipedia:CNN|CNN]]|archivedate=20201129181527}}</ref>

